{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":19651,"name":"Charles","username":"zedraken","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/zedraken/{size}/328_2.png","created_at":"2017-07-28T05:52:22.060Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eHi folks,\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI am currently using Blender to create a simple model for which I apply a texture (it is a single image representing a metal floor). Still under Blender, I play with the “Image Mapping-\u0026gt;Repeat” parameters to have my texture repeated several times over both X and Y directions.\u003cbr\u003e\nThis appears fine in Blender when I render it.\u003cbr\u003e\nThen, I export to Urho3D using the Urho3D exporter which also works fine. I get no errors and the texture is exported along with the material.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHere is the content of my material XML file that references the texture to be used.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode\u003e\u0026lt;material\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;technique name=\"Techniques/Diff.xml\"/\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;texture name=\"Textures/MetalFloorsBare0049.jpg\" unit=\"diffuse\"/\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;parameter name=\"MatDiffColor\" value=\"0.0564704 0.0564704 0.0564704 1\"/\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;parameter name=\"MatSpecColor\" value=\"0 0 0 250\"/\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;/material\u0026gt;\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIt clearly appears that there are no “tiling” or “repeating” information coming from Blender. When I run my Urho3D app that displays the model, the texture is not repeated.\u003cbr\u003e\nIn such a case, I assume that it is useless to try to configure texture repetition in Blender since it is not exported. Is my assumption correct ?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIn any cases, how can I proceed to be able to get a texture repetition in my XML file ? Or do I have to do thing in another way ?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThanks a lot for your answers !\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eCharles\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-07-28T05:53:01.249Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":408,"reads":83,"readers_count":82,"score":2056.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":3393,"topic_slug":"repeating-textures","display_username":"Charles","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":527,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":19653,"name":"Alex Piola","username":"Alex-Doc","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/alex-doc/{size}/503_2.png","created_at":"2017-07-28T07:16:22.458Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eHi, your assumption is right, the blender exporter doesn’t seems to be exporting the UV offset:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIt’s not really intuitive to find but see how it works in \u003ca href=\"https://github.com/urho3d/Urho3D/blob/master/bin/Data/Materials/StoneTiled.xml\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003eStoneTiled.xml\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003e    \u0026lt;parameter name=\"UOffset\" value=\"4 0 0 0\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;parameter name=\"VOffset\" value=\"0 4 0 0\" /\u0026gt;\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWhere “4” is the tiling scale.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBy setting those two parameters in your material, you should be able to get the tiling.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI hope this helps!\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-07-29T09:05:14.492Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":5,"reads":77,"readers_count":76,"score":40.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":3393,"topic_slug":"repeating-textures","display_username":"Alex Piola","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":2,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://github.com/urho3d/Urho3D/blob/master/bin/Data/Materials/StoneTiled.xml","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"urho3d/Urho3D","clicks":22}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":752,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":true},{"id":19657,"name":"","username":"Mike","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/m/58f4c7/{size}.png","created_at":"2017-07-28T09:36:47.695Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eAlthough ‘Image Mapping-\u0026gt;Repeat’, ‘Mapping-\u0026gt;Offset’ and ‘Mapping-\u0026gt;Size’ support could be easily added to the exporter, they have several drawbacks:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003ethey don’t appear in the 3D viewport (you have to render the scene for them to show up)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e‘Repeat’ only supports integer values, which means the texture aspect ratio is not preserved\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e‘Offset’ and ‘Size’ are a bit tough to tweak (especially since you have to render to see the changes)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFor these reasons, I’d recommend to scale and translate your UVs in the UV/Image Editor instead.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-07-29T09:05:14.420Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":4,"reads":74,"readers_count":73,"score":34.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":3393,"topic_slug":"repeating-textures","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"Contributor","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":true,"admin":false,"staff":true,"user_id":9,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":19677,"name":"Charles","username":"zedraken","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/zedraken/{size}/328_2.png","created_at":"2017-07-29T09:04:24.419Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eThanks for your answers.\u003cbr\u003e\nFor the moment, I overscaled my UVs in Blender and kept repetition parameters to 1 (as Mike suggested). However, I will also give a try to the solution given by Alex-Doc.\u003cbr\u003e\nThank you again for your help !\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-07-29T09:05:09.821Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":64,"readers_count":63,"score":12.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":3393,"topic_slug":"repeating-textures","display_username":"Charles","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":527,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":21598,"name":"Octavian","username":"stark7","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/stark7/{size}/998_2.png","created_at":"2017-11-08T00:55:42.081Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eIs there a way to repeat the texture for a scaling model instead of having the texture stretched?\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-11-08T00:55:42.081Z","reply_count":2,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":55,"readers_count":54,"score":31.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":3393,"topic_slug":"repeating-textures","display_username":"Octavian","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":733,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":21601,"name":"","username":"Don","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/don/{size}/755_2.png","created_at":"2017-11-08T05:16:44.356Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eIf you are talking about having a model automatically repeat a texture as it is scaled during runtime, I don’t know if there is currently a way to do this in engine. With that said, if the scalings are predetermined before runtime, you could adjust the UV mappings in Blender. Otherwise, a runtime effect for tiling could be done without too much trouble in shaders. Hope this helps.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-11-08T05:16:44.356Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":5,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":55,"readers_count":54,"score":11.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":3393,"topic_slug":"repeating-textures","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_use